songs.title: Focus
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Looking in the mirror and I am liking what I see
Thought I told you'll once before, can't nobody f*ck with me
I was raised in BAY, but was made in SAC
Man the glow up been to be real, bet ya'll liking what ya'll see
Yeah my mama is a soldier and my daddy is a G
When you put them two together, what you think that made me?
She had me at 17, made it worse, she did her thing
Yeah you did it, love you mama, look how I turned out to be
I did 2 years in Diego and 3 at USC
That's a beauty, that's a beast, I bet her brain is so OD
Said a prayer to the Lord, keep me safe from enemies
Then I start losing friends, I thank God for for clarity, uh

[Hook]
Focus, keep me focus
All these little things man, they keep me focus
Focus, keep me focus
All these little things man, they keep me focus

[Verse 2]
Any nigga play or disrespect me, he regret me, wish he kept me
People question how they lost me, make it hard, they can't forget me. Wasn't she with so and so? Now she out with who a who?
Niggas hate when you go do what they would do if they was you
I said I am married to the game, 'cause the blood that's in my veins
No, my father ain't no pimp, but he thought me the pimp way
Can't no nigga disrespect you, keep these hoes up in they place
You know you doing something right when they love you out of hate
I said my father ain't no pimp, but he thought me the pimp way
Can't no nigga disrespect you, keep these hoes up in they place
You know you doing something right when they love you out of hate
You see I read between the lines I know you' praise was really shade nigga

[Hook]
Focus, keep me focus
All these little things man, they keep me focus
Focus, keep me focus
All these little things man, they keep me focus
